3_376_Fig4_HTML.png" alt="" loading="lazy" width="312" height="145"></picture><span class="u-visually-hidden" id="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-4-1">The alternative text for this image may have been generated using AI.</span></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-5"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig5" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 5: Operando SXRD of the disordered CoOOH skin layer that indicates a spatially extended OER-active interphase.</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs44160-023-00376-6/MediaObjects/44160_2023_376_Fig5_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-5-1" src="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs44160-023-00376-6/MediaObjects/44160_2023_376_Fig5_HTML.png" alt="" loading="lazy" width="312" height="137"></picture><span class="u-visually-hidden" id="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-5-1">The alternative text for this image may have been generated using AI.</span></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-6"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig6" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 6: Operando characterization of CoO<sub><i>x</i></sub>(OH)<sub><i>y</i></sub> nanoparticles showing a size-dependent oxidation leading to near-surface Co–O bond contraction due to the accumulation of oxidative charge and deprotonation.</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-stati